<h3 id=3D"id-01.SD:Transfers&amp;paymentstoexistingbeneficiary[ERM24E4Aug20=
24]-Constraints&amp;Dependencies">Constraints &amp; Dependencies</h3>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 364.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 372.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 480.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 361.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 184.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Ref #</st=
rong></p><p>[A-###, C-###, D-###]</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Considera=
tions Type</strong></p><p>[Assumptions, Constraints, Dependencies]</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Descripti=
on</strong></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Notes</st=
rong></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Date</str=
ong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C-001</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Constraint</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>For the first ite=
ration of this feature, the Beneficiary Datastore and associated INF api wi=
ll not be in scope.&nbsp;</p><p>The EXP API will return locally saved (aka =
encrypted property file via Mesh Encrypt) beneficiaries</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2023-11-27" class=3D"date-past">27 Nov 2023</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C-002</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Constraint</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>For the first ite=
ration of this feature, we will not be able to fetch the 'FROM' accounts in=
 real time.&nbsp;</p><p>The EXP API will return locally saved (aka encrypte=
d property file via Mesh Encrypt) arrangements.</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2023-11-27" class=3D"date-past">27 Nov 2023</time>&nbs=
p;&nbsp;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C-003</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Constraint</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The Payment Initi=
ation CAP API cannot provide a set list of possible 'reasons' why a payment=
 has failed. This is because the error code is coming from the core ledger =
(10x) and from FIS. They need to provide a definitive list of options.</p><=
/td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2023-11-30" class=3D"date-past">30 Nov 2023</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>D-001</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Dependency</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>We need onboard i=
nto the Mesh UI Audit Event to cater for the initiate payment scenario&nbsp=
;</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2023-11-27" class=3D"date-past">27 Nov 2023</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">D-002</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Dependency</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">There is a dependenc=
y on the CAP Initiate Payment API. It needs to support on-platform and on-m=
e type of payments</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>A-001</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Assumptions</p></=
td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">The MFE UI only need=
s to handle real-time payment error&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Either get a Approve=
d message, submitted or rejected synchronously&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2023-08-14" class=3D"date-past">14 Aug 2023</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>A-002</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Assumptions</p></=
td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>If a transfer jou=
rney is initiated, the channels will add a '<strong>on-me</strong>' transac=
tion code to the request. Any other type of payment we do not need to speci=
fy the transaction code</p><p><br></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">The Transaction code=
 will be based of on how the UI was initiated.&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2023-08-14" class=3D"date-past">14 Aug 2023</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>A-003</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Assumption</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>All the customerT=
ypes will be 'Organisation'</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2024-02-07" class=3D"date-past">07 Feb 2024</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"id-01.SD:Transfers&amp;paymentstoexistingbeneficiary[ERM24E4Aug20=
24]-OutofScopeforMay">Out of Scope for May</h2>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Managing Beneficiaries (CRUD)</li>
<li><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Usage of a Channel Operation Dat=
astore to link beneficiary payments to a receipt number</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">NPP (Off-Group)</span></li>
<li>Integration of a Payment Receipt Generation API</li>
<li><p>Receiving RAR token (no entitlement check)</p></li>
<li>Server-side search, sort, and pagination (entitlement engine)</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"id-01.SD:Transfers&amp;paymentstoexistingbeneficiary[ERM24E4Aug20=
24]-DeltarequiredforNPPUplift">Delta required for NPP Uplift</h1>
<h2 id=3D"id-01.SD:Transfers&amp;paymentstoexistingbeneficiary[ERM24E4Aug20=
24]-Overview">Overview</h2>
<p>To enable NPP payments using this implementation, the following changes =
need to be applied</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>In the<strong> request payload</strong>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><=
strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"6f7f2896-2f12-463b=
-ae01-5938382ca297">Payment Reference</span></strong><span class=3D"inline-=
comment-marker" data-ref=3D"6f7f2896-2f12-463b-ae01-5938382ca297"> =3D </sp=
an></span></span><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"6f7f2896=
-2f12-463b-ae01-5938382ca297">Unique identification</span> entered by the i=
nitiating customer to unambiguously identify the transaction from their per=
spective. his identification is passed on, unchanged, throughout the entire=
 end-to-end chain.</li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Debtor:</span>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Financial Institution BIC, to be pro=
vided by the Channel (i.e. WPACAU2SONE for Cash Platform).</span></li>
</ul></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Creditor:</span>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Financial Inst=
itution BIC, to be provided by the Channel (i.e. WPACAU2SXXX).</span></li>
</ul></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">Clearing Scheme:</span>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span><span class=3D"ui-provider ed =
btd bpu bxi bxj bxk bxl bxm bxn bxo bxp bxq bxr bxs bxt bxu bxv bxw bxx bxy=
 bxz bya byb byc byd bye byf byg byh byi byj byk byl bym byn">'npp.clear.01=
-x2p1.01'</span></span></span></li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span><span class=3D"ui-provider ed =
btd bpu bxi bxj bxk bxl bxm bxn bxo bxp bxq bxr bxs bxt bxu bxv bxw bxx bxy=
 bxz bya byb byc byd bye byf byg byh byi byj byk byl bym byn">In the <stron=
g>response handling</strong>: new logic to implement to determine which mes=
sage to display</span></span></span>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><span><span class=3D"ui-provider ed bld bhj cth cti ctj ctk ctl ctm ctn=
 cto ctp ctq ctr cts ctt ctu ctv ctw ctx cty ctz cua cub cuc cud cue cuf cu=
g cuh cui cuj cuk cul cum">For the scenario where DebitPosting =3D Successf=
ul, the channel will only see ACSC.</span></span></li>
<li><p>What status's can we expect if DebitPosting =3D success but NPP is d=
own / or any other issue downstream? A<span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;=
">nswer: ACSC.</span></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
