<h1 id=3D"id-01.SD:Transfers&amp;paymentstoexistingbeneficiary[ERM24E4Aug20=
24]-ConsumptionofServiceLayers">Consumption of Service Layers</h1>
<h3 id=3D"id-01.SD:Transfers&amp;paymentstoexistingbeneficiary[ERM24E4Aug20=
24]-Galaxy-PaymentExperienceAPI"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">Gala=
xy-Payment Experience API</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);font-size: 16.0px;font-weight: bold;let=
ter-spacing: -0.006em;">API Overview</span></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 110=
2.47px;">
<thead class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,0);">API Name</span></th>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">exp-galaxy-payment-v=
2</td>
</tr>
</thead>
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 357.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 745.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,0);">Base URL</span></th>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">/exp/galaxy/payment/=
v2</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,0);">API Description &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></th>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(0,51,102);">This API allows interaction for the Galaxy SPA with th=
e Payment Initiation API and allows retrieving of beneficiaries for the log=
ged in user. It supports getting arrangements as well</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh">API Layer&nbsp;</th>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Experience</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,0);">Swagger Location</span></th>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><a href=3D"https://b=
itbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/galaxy-payment-microfrontend=
/browse/swagger.yaml" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Link</a></td=
>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,0);">Document Status</span></th>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-moved">PENDING</span=
></p>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>Endpoints:</p>
<ul>
<li><span class=3D"opblock-summary-path" style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);"><s=
pan>/healthcheck</span></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">GET /arrangements</span>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">&nbsp;Integrates 1:1 with <a href=
=3D"/display/ARTC/cap-prodsvcadm-proddealacctadm-instl-arrngmntsvcng-v1">ca=
p-prodsvcadm-proddealacctadm-instl-arrngmntsvcng-v1</a></span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">Returns 'FROM' accounts&nbsp;</sp=
an></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">Locally hardcoded bsb+account num=
bers to fetch more information downstream</span></li>
</ul></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);"><span class=3D"opblock-summary-pa=
th" style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);"><span>GET /beneficiaries</span></span><=
/span>
<ul>
<li>To retrieve beneficiaries from datastore&nbsp;</li>
</ul></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);"><span class=3D"opblock-summary-pa=
th" style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);"><span>POST /payments</span></span></spa=
n>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">Published UI Audit events</span><=
/li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">Integrates with Receipt Number Ge=
neration API</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(59,65,81);">Integrates with Payment Initiatio=
n API</span></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"id-01.SD:Transfers&amp;paymentstoexistingbeneficiary[ERM24E4Aug20=
24]-PaymentInitiationCAPAPI"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">Payment =
Initiation CAP API</span></h3>
<p><strong><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">API Overview</span></strong><=
/p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 110=
2.47px;">
<thead class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,0);">API Name</span></th>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><em style=3D"text-al=
ign: left;"><strong><span>&nbsp;</span>W1C Payment Initiation API <a style=
=3D"text-align: left;" href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/project=
s/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-prodsvcfulflmnt-pymntprocsng-pymntinit-v1-api/browse?at=
=3Dswagger-review" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">wdp-cap-prodsvc=
fulflmnt-pymntprocsng-pymntinit-v1-api</a></strong></em></td>
</tr>
</thead>
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 357.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 745.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,0);">Base URL</span></th>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">cap/prodsvcfulflmnt/=
pymntprocsng/pymntinit/v1</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,0);">API Description &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></th>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p style=3D"text-ali=
gn: left;">Register a new W1C Customer Credit Transfer i.e. initiation of a=
 single credit transfer instruction.</p><p style=3D"text-align: left;">This=
 API is called by the Channel Experience API.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh">API Layer&nbsp;</th>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">CAP</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(0,0,0);">Swagger Location</span></th>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><a href=3D"/display/ARTC/Payment+Initiation+API+v1.0">Payment Initiation=
 API v1.0</a></p>
<p><!--
  ~ Copyright (c) 2014 by Mibex Software GmbH, Zurich, Switzerland.
  ~
  ~ All rights reserved.
  ~
  ~ This product is the proprietary and sole property of Mibex Software Gmb=
H.
  ~ Use, duplication or dissemination is forbidden and is subject to prior
  ~ written consent of Mibex Software GmbH (office@mibex.ch).
  --> <!--
  ~ Copyright (c) 2014 by Mibex Software GmbH, Zurich, Switzerland.=20
  ~
  ~ All rights reserved.=20
  ~
  ~ This product is the proprietary and sole property of Mibex Software Gmb=
H.=20
  ~ Use, duplication or dissemination is forbidden and is subject to prior=
=20
  ~ written consent of Mibex Software GmbH (office@mibex.ch).
  --></p>
<div class=3D"file-macro-container include4confluence include4confluence-co=
ntent">
<div class=3D"include4confluence-panel panel" id=3D"include4confluence-bord=
er">
<div class=3D"">
<div class=3D"include4confluence-header">
<a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-cap-=
prodsvcfulflmnt-pymntprocsng-pymntinit-v1-api" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"nor=
eferrer">WDP / wdp-cap-prodsvcfulflmnt-pymntprocsng-pymntinit-v1-api /</a> =
<b> <a href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP/repos/wdp-=
cap-prodsvcfulflmnt-pymntprocsng-pymntinit-v1-api/browse/openapi.yaml?at=3D=
refs/heads/swagger-review" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer">openapi.yam=
l</a> </b>
<div class=3D"include4confluence-no-wrap include4confluence-meta-branch-tag=
-info">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-devtools-branch"></span=
> swagger-review
</div>
<div style=3D"clear:both"></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"include4confluence-panel-content-container ">
<div class=3D"include4confluence-code-content">
<pre style=3D"font-size: 12px;">openapi: 3.0.3
info:
  title: Payment Initiation API
  contact:
    url: "https://mesh.westpac.com.au/components/apis/cap-prodsvcfulflmnt-p=
ymntprocsng-pymntinit-v1"
  description: Payment Capability API to process payment initiation and ret=
urns.
  version: 1.0.0
  x-baseTypesVersion: 0.12.0 # The version of the base type on which the sp=
ec is base

servers:
  - url: "/cap/prodsvcfulflmnt/pymntprocsng/pymntinit/v1"

security:
  - BasicAuth: [ ]

tags:
  - name: postPayments
  - name: PaymentIdentifierGenerator
  - name: PaymentReturnInitiation
  - name: HealthCheck

paths:
  /payments:
    post:
      tags:
        - postPayments
      description: &gt;
        This endpoint initiate a credit transfer payment
      operationId: postPayments
      parameters:
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/userId'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/userIdScheme'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/idempotencyKey'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/customerType'
      requestBody:
        description: &gt;
          Initiate the payment throught FIS POM API and return the code for=
 success or error
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/PaymentInitiationRequest'
        required: true
      responses:
        '201':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/201PostPaymentsResponse'
        '202':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/202PostPaymentsResponse'
        '400':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/400PostPaymentsErrorResponse'
        '500':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/500ErrorResponse'
  /paymentIdentifierGenerator:
    post:
      tags:
        - PaymentIdentifierGenerator
      description: &gt;
        This endpoint get a payment Identifier for a single credit transfer=
 payment
      operationId: PaymentIdentifierGenerator
      requestBody:
        description: &gt;
          Generate the Payment Identifier for a payment and return the code=
 for success or error
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/PaymentIdGenerationRequest'
        required: true
      responses:
        '201':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/201PostPaymentIDGenerationResponse'
        '400':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/400getPaymentsIdGenerationErrorResp=
onse'
        '500':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/500PaymentsIdGenerationErrorRespons=
e'

  /paymentReturns:
    post:
      tags:
        - PaymentReturnInitiation
      description: &gt;
        This endpoint is to register a new W1C Payment Return. i.e. Initiat=
ion of a single payment return.
      operationId: PaymentReturnInitiation
      parameters:
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/userId'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/userIdScheme'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/idempotencyKey'
        - $ref: '#/components/parameters/customerType'
      requestBody:
        description: &gt;
          Initiate the Payment return for a payment and return the code for=
 success or error
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/PaymentReturnInitiationRequest'
        required: true
      responses:
        '201':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/201PostPaymentReturnResponse'
        '202':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/201PostPaymentReturnResponse'
        '400':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/400PaymentsReturnErrorResponse'
        '500':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/500ErrorResponse'

  /healthcheck:
    get:
      tags:
        - HealthCheck
      description: retrieves HealthCheck Summary of API.
      operationId: getHealthCheckStatus
      responses:
        '200':
          $ref: '#/components/responses/200healthCheckStatusResponse'
components:
  securitySchemes:
    BasicAuth:
      $ref: "https://schema.mesh.westpac.com.au/platform/contracts/0.12.0/o=
penapi-base.yaml#/components/securitySchemes/BasicAuth"

  schemas:
    healthCheckStatus:
      type: object
      properties:
        status:
          type: string
          enum:
            - success
      description: healthcheck status

    PaymentInitiationRequest:
      type: object
      description: Payment Initiation Request.
      required:
        - messageIdentification
        - creationDateTime
        - initiatingParty
        - debtorAccount
        - creditTransferTransactionInformation
        - supplementaryData
      properties:
        messageIdentification:
          type: string
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 35
          example: c541b60a0cdd42d2a9dd7a410d992586
          pattern: ^[0-9a-f]{8}([0-9a-f]{4}){3}[0-9a-f]{12}$
          description: &gt;-
            Point to point reference, as assigned by the instructing party,=
 and sent to the next party in the chain to unambiguously identify the mess=
age. The instructing party has to make sure that messageId is unique per in=
structed party for a pre-agreed period.
        creationDateTime:
          type: string
          format: date-time
          description: &gt;-
            Date and time at which the message was  created. &lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to set this field to today's date.
        initiatingParty:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/InitiatingParty'
        paymentInformation:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/paymentInformationRequestObject'
        paymentTypeInformation:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/paymentTypeInformationObject'
        debtor:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/debtorObject'
        debtorAccount:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/accountObject'
        debtorAgent:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/debtorAgentObject'
        instructionForDebtorAgent:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/instructionForDebtorAgentObject'

        creditTransferTransactionInformation:
          type: array
          items:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/creditTransferInformationItems'
        supplementaryData:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/PaymentSupplementaryDataObject'

    instructionForDebtorAgentObject:
      type: string
      maxLength: 140
      pattern: '^[a-zA-Z0-9\\s-]*$'
      description: &gt;-
        Further information related to the processing of the payment instru=
ction, that may need to be acted upon by the debtor agent, depending on agr=
eement between debtor and the debtor agent. When present, it applies to ALL=
 credit transfer transaction information occurrences, present in the paymen=
t information. &lt;br&gt;
        Usage- For future use.
    debtorAgentObject:
      type: object
      required:
        - BICFI
      properties:
        BICFI:
          type: string
          maxLength: 11
          description: &gt;-
            Code allocated to a financial institution by the ISO 9362 Regis=
tration Authority as described in ISO 9362 "Banking - Banking telecommunica=
tion messages - Business identifier code (BIC)".&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to set this field to the new WIB BIC 'WPACAU2SONE=
'.

    accountObject:
      type: object
      required:
        - identification
        - schemeName
        - issuer
      properties:
        identification:
          type: string
          maxLength: 34
          description: &gt;-
            Full account number including BSB (without any separators or sp=
aces).&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to map debit account number to this field.

        schemeName:
          type: string
          enum:
            - BBAN
          description: &gt;-
            Name of the identification scheme, in a coded form as published=
 in an external list.&lt;br&gt;
             Usage- Caller to set this field to 'BBAN' to represent Austral=
ian Bank-State-Branch Code (BSB) identification.
        issuer:
          type: string
          maxLength: 35
          description: &gt;-
            Entity that assigns the identification.&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to map this field to the 6-digit BSB number of th=
e debit account.
        name:
          type: string
          maxLength: 140
          description: &gt;-
            Name by which a party is known, and which is usually used to id=
entify that party. For NPP payment, this is the Full Legal Account Name (FL=
AN). &lt;br&gt;
            Usage- For NPP payments, this field is expected to be provided =
by the payment enrichment system.

        type:
          type: string
          maxLength: 35
          description: &gt;-
            Debtor's account type represented as Canonical Product Code (CP=
C).&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- For future use.
    paymentInformationRequestObject:
      type: object
      description: &gt;-
        Set of characteristics that applies to the payment instruction.
      required:
        - paymentMethod
        - requestedExecutionDate
      properties:
        paymentMethod:
          type: string
          example: TRF
          enum:
            - TRF
            - CHK
            - TRA
          description: &gt;-
            Specifies the means of payment that will be used to move the am=
ount of money.&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to set this field to 'TRF'.
        requestedExecutionDate:
          type: string
          format: date
          description: &gt;-
            Date at which the initiating party requests the clearing agent =
to process the payment. This is the date on which the debtor's account is t=
o be debited.Example- "2016-03-16".&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to set this field

        numberOfTransactions:
          type: string
          pattern: '[0-9]{1,15}$'
          description: &gt;-
            Number of individual transactions contained in the payment info=
rmation group.&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to set this field to 1 to indicate there's only o=
ne transaction in the payment. For Bulk payment in the future, this field w=
ill need to be set by the caller to the actual number of transactions in th=
e bulk instruction.

        controlSum:
          type: string
          description: &gt;-
            Total of all individual amounts included in the group, irrespec=
tive of currencies.&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- For future use.
    debtorObject:
      type: object
      description: Party that owes an amount of money to the (ultimate) cre=
ditor.
      properties:
        name:
          type: string
          maxLength: 140
          description: &gt;-
            Name by which a party is known, and which is usually used to id=
entify sending party.&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to map debtor's name to this field.
        identification:
          type: string
          maxLength: 35
          description: &gt;-
            Unique and unambiguous identification of a person. For example,=
 CIS Key of the debtor account.&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to map debtor's identification to this field.
        issuer:
          type: string
          maxLength: 35
          description: &gt;-
            Entity that assigns the identification.=20
            Example- WPAC &lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to set this field to 'WPAC'.
   =20

    PaymentInitiationResponse:
      type: object
      properties:
        data:
          type: object
          properties:
            paymentStatusReport:
              $ref: "#/components/schemas/PaymentStatusReportObject"

        result:
          type: object
          properties:
            errors:
              type: array
              items:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorPartialSuccess'


    PaymentStatusReportObject:
      type: object
      description: Synchronous response to Submit Payment Details Request.
      required:
        - groupInformation
      properties:
        messageIdentification:
          type: string
          maxLength: 35
          description: Point to point reference, as assigned by the instruc=
ting party, and sent to the next party in the chain to identify the message=
.
        creationDateTime:
          type: string
          format : date-time
          description: Date and time at which the message was created.
        groupInformation:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/GroupInformationObject2'
        paymentInformation:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/paymentInformationResponseObject'

    paymentInformationResponseObject:
      type: object
      description: Information concerning the original payment information,=
 to which the status report message refers.
      required:
        - paymentInformationStatus
        - transactionInformation
      properties:
        paymentInformationStatus:
          type: string
          description: Specifies the ISO status of the payment. Usage- Poss=
ible values -&lt;br&gt; ACSC- Accepted Settlement Completed (success) &lt;b=
r&gt; ACSP- Accepted Settlement In Process (auto retry in progress in case =
of technical failure)&lt;br&gt; RJCT- Rejected

        statusReasonInformation:
          type: array
          items:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/statusReasonInformation'

        transactionInformation:
          type: array
          items:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/TransactionInformationItems2'
        supplementaryData:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/supplementaryDataResponseObject'
    supplementaryDataResponseObject:
      type: object
      properties:
        paymentId:
          type: string
          description: Usage- Echoed from the request.

    TransactionInformationItems2:
      description: Provides information on the original transactions to whi=
ch the status report message refers.
      properties:
        originalEndToEndIdentification:
          type: string
          description: Usage- Echoed from the request.
        transactionStatus:
          type: string
          description: Specifies the ISO status of the credit transaction w=
ithin the payment, in case of on-us payments.
            &lt;br&gt;
            Usage-  Possible values-
            ACSC - Accepted Settlement Completed (success)
            RJCT - Rejected (posting rejected)
            ACSP - Accepted Settlement In Process (auto retry in progress i=
n case of technical failure
        statusReasonInformation:
          type: array
          items:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/statusReasonInformation'

    GroupInformationObject:
      type: object
      description: Provides details on the original group, to which the mes=
sage refers
      properties:
        originalCreationDateTime:
          type: string
          format: date-time
          description: Date and time at which the original message was crea=
ted.
        groupStatus:
          type: string
          description: Specifies the ISO status at the group level.Usage- F=
or future use.
        statusReasonInformation:
          type: array
          items:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/statusReasonInformation'

    GroupInformationObject2:
      allOf:
        - $ref: '#/components/schemas/GroupInformationObject'
        - type: object
          required:
            - originalCreationDateTime
            - originalNumberOfTransactions
            - groupStatus
          properties:
            originalNumberOfTransactions:
              type: string
              description: Number of individual transactions contained in t=
he original message.
            originalControlSum:
              type: string
              description: Total of all individual amounts included in the =
original message, irrespective of currencies.

    InitiatingParty:
      description: Party that initiates the payment. This can either be the=
 debtor or the party that initiates the credit transfer on behalf of the de=
btor.
      required:
        - identification
      type: object
      properties:
        name:
          type: string
          maxLength: 140
          description: Initiating party's full name.&lt;br&gt;Usage- Caller=
 to map initiating party's name to this field.
        identification:
          type: string
          maxLength: 36
          description: Initiating party identifier, assigned by the institu=
tion. i.e. Initiating party CIS key or Group Network id.&lt;br&gt;Usage- Ca=
ller to map initiating party's identification to this field.
    creditTransferInformationItems:
      description: Provides information on the individual transaction(s) in=
cluded in the message.
      required:
        - instructedAmount
        - creditor
        - creditorAgent
      type: object
      properties:
        instructionIdentification:
          type: string
          minLength: 20
          maxLength: 35
          example: c541b60a0cdd42d2a9dd7a410d992586
          pattern: ^[0-9a-f]{8}([0-9a-f]{4}){3}[0-9a-f]{12}$
          description: &gt;-
            Unique identification as assigned by an instructing party for a=
n instructed party to unambiguously identify the instruction.
        endToEndIdentification:
          type: string
          maxLength: 35
          description: &gt;-
            A reference assigned by the initiating party to unambiguously i=
dentify the payment. This identifier is passed on unchanged throughout the =
entire end-to-end payment flow. The end-to-end identification can be used f=
or reconciliation or to link tasks relating to the payment. It can be inclu=
ded in several messages related to the payment.&lt;br&gt;
            Example- INV-123456790&lt;br&gt;
             Usage- Caller to map customer's payment reference to this fiel=
d.  For NPP Osko payments.
             May only be provided if customerType in the header is set to '=
Organisation'.
             Must be set to 'NOTPROVIDED' if customerType in the header is =
set to 'Individual'.
        paymentTypeInformation:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/paymentTypeInformationObject'

        instructedAmount:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/instructedAmountObject'

        creditor:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/creditorObject'
        creditorAccount:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/accountObject'

        creditorAgent:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/debtorAgentObject'
        remittanceInformation:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/remittanceInformationObject'

        instructionForDebtorAgent:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/instructionForDebtorAgentObject'

        supplementaryData:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/supplementaryDataObject'
    paymentTypeInformationObject:
      description: Set of elements used to further specify the type of tran=
saction.
      type: object
      properties:
        serviceLevel:
          maxLength: 35
          type: string
          description: &gt;-
            Specifies a pre-agreed service or level of service between the =
parties.&lt;br&gt;
            NORM - For 'Attended' transaction. Attended payments are define=
d as Payments whereby the sending participant requires a real-time response=
 to their payment instruction
             &lt;br&gt;UNAT - For 'Unattended' transaction. Unattended paym=
ents are defined as Payments whereby the sending participant does not requi=
re a real-time response to their payment instruction.&lt;br&gt;
             Usage- Caller to set this field to 'NORM'.&lt;br&gt;
           =20
             For credit transfer transactions- Specifies a pre-agreed servi=
ce or level of service between the parties.&lt;br&gt;
           =20
            Usage- Caller to set this field to 'npp.clear.01-x2p1.01' for N=
PP Osko payments.
        localInstrument:
          maxLength: 35
          type: string
          description: &gt;-
            Specifies the type of local instrument being requested by the i=
nitiating party.&lt;br&gt;=20
            Usage- For future use.

        categoryPurpose:
          type: string
          maxLength: 35
          description: &gt;-
            Specifies the high-level purpose of the instruction based on a =
set of pre-defined categories. This is used by the initiating party to prov=
ide information concerning the processing of the payment. &lt;br&gt;
            Usage- For future use.

        instructionPriority:
          type: string
          description: &gt;-
            Indicator of the urgency or order of importance that the instru=
cting party would like the instructed party to apply to the processing of t=
he instruction. The possible values are-&lt;br&gt;
              HIGH: High. &lt;br&gt;
              NORM: Normal.&lt;br&gt;
              Usage- For future use.
          enum:
            - HIGH
            - NORM
    instructedAmountObject:
      $ref: '#/components/schemas/CurrencyAmount'
    creditorObject:
      type: object
      required:
        - name
      properties:
        name:
          type: string
          maxLength: 140
          description: &gt;-
            Name by which a party is known, and which is usually used to id=
entify that party. (Creditor name or Alias Short Name).&lt;br&gt; Usage- Ca=
ller to map creditor's name to this field.

    statusReasonInformation:
      description: Status reason information
      type: object
      properties:
        reason:
          type: string
          description: &gt;-
            Status reason description.
           =20
              Group status reason can have values -
                AccountEligibilityFailure
                DuplicatePayment
                ExternalValidationEnrichmentFailed
                PostingFailed
                PostingSucceeded
                ValidationFailure
           =20
              Instruction status reason can have values -
                AccountEligibilityFailure
                InsufficientAccountBalance
                DebitPostingFailed
                DebitPostingSucceeded
                ExternalValidationEnrichmentFailed
                FraudCheckDeclined
                FraudCheckDelayed
                FraudCheckNotAvailable
                FraudCheckOnHold
                FraudCheckReferred
                FundsReservationFailed
                FundsReservationSucceeded
                InvalidExecutionDate
                ValidationFailure
           =20
              Transaction status reason can have values -
                ClearingAndSettlementRejected
                AccountEligibilityFailure
                CreditPostingAborted
                CreditPostingFailed
                SchemeDeterminationFailed
                ValidationFailure
        additionalInformation:
          type: string
          description: Further information about the above status reason fr=
om downstream.

    remittanceInformationObject:
      description: Remittance information to be supplied with the          =
      payment.
      type: object
      properties:
        unstructured:
          type: array
          maxItems: 2
          items:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/unstructuredItems'
    unstructuredItems:
      type: string
      maxLength: 140
      description: Remittance information to be supplied with a payment to =
assist the recipient to determine the intended purpose of the payment. Ther=
e are two lines of 140 characters.&lt;br&gt;Usage- Caller to map credit des=
cription (statement narrative) to this field.

    supplementaryDataObject:
      type: object
      description: Additional Westpac Data Elements to support the         =
       PAYMENT transaction (Credit).
      properties:
        beneficiaryId:
          type: string
          maxLength: 36
          description: Usage- Caller to map this field with the Beneficiary=
 Id of the recipient for the On-Platform payment
        templateId:
          type: string
          maxLength: 36
          description:   Usage- Caller to pa this field with the Template I=
d of the recipient for the On-Platform payment.

    PaymentSupplementaryDataObject:
      type: object
      description: Additional Westpac Data Elements to support the         =
       PAYMENT Instruction (Debit).
      required:
        - paymentId
      properties:
        paymentId:
          type: string
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 36
          description: &gt;-
            Payment Identifier, also known as Receipt Number.&lt;br&gt;
        debitDescription:
          type: string
          maxLength: 35
          description: &gt;-
            The reference assigned by the sending party for the payment.&lt=
;br&gt;Usage- Caller to map debit description (statement narrative) to this=
 field.

    CurrencyAmount:
      description: currency amount details.
      type: object
      required:
        - amount
        - currency
      properties:
        amount:
          pattern: '\d{1,13}\.?\d{0,3}$'
          type: string
          description: The payment amount before deduction of charges, expr=
essed in the currency as ordered by the initiating party.&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to map payment amount to this field.
        currency:
          type: string
          minLength: 3
          maxLength: 3
          description: A code allocated to a currency by a Maintenance Agen=
cy under an international identification scheme, as described in the latest=
 edition of the international standard ISO 4217 =E2=80=9CCodes for the repr=
esentation of currencies and funds=E2=80=9D.&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to set 'AUD' to this field.
          example: AUD

    PaymentIdGenerationRequest:
      type: object
      description: Payment Id Generation Request.
      required:
        - channelId

      properties:
        channelId:
          type: string
          example: WP
          description: &gt;-
            &lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to set this field
            'WP' for W1C Portal
            'QV' for QValent
            'SW' for Swift
            'OB' for Open Banking
            'WS' for W1C Service
          enum:
            - WP
            - QV
            - SW
            - OB
            - WS
    PaymentIDResponse:
      type: object
      description: Synchronous response for Payment Id to Submit Payment De=
tails Request.
      properties:
        data:
          type: object
          required:
            - id
            - creationDateTime
          properties:
            paymentId:
              type: string
              maxLength: 36
              description: ID generated for this request.
            creationDateTime:
              type: string
              format : date-time
              description: Date and time of the ID generation.
    Error:
      required:
        - code
        - message
      type: object
      properties:
        code:
          type: integer
          description: Error Code.
          format: int32
        message:
          type: string
          description: Error Message
        details:
          type: string
          description: Detailed information about the error
      description: Represent an individual error.
    ErrorResponse:
      type: object
      properties:
        result:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorResult'
    ErrorResult:
      type: object
      properties:
        errors:
          type: array
          items:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
    ErrorPartialSuccess:
      required:
        - code
        - message
      type: object
      properties:
        code:
          type: integer
          description: Error Code.
          format: int32
          example: 1004
        message:
          type: string
          description: Error Message from POM
          example: need one
        details:
          type: string
          description: Detailed information about the error from POM
          example: need one

    PaymentReturnInitiationRequest:
      type: object
      description: Payment Return Request
      required:
        - messageIdentification
        - creationDateTime
        - numberOfTransactions
        - settlementInformation
      properties:
        messageIdentification:
          type: string
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 35
          example: c541b60a0cdd42d2a9dd7a410d992586
          pattern: ^[0-9a-f]{8}([0-9a-f]{4}){3}[0-9a-f]{12}$
          description: &gt;-
            Point to point reference, as assigned by the instructing party,=
 and sent to the next party in the chain to unambiguously identify the mess=
age. The instructing party has to make sure that messageId is unique per in=
structed party for a pre-agreed period.
            &lt;br&gt;
            W1C: Caller to generate this field.
        creationDateTime:
          type: string
          format: date-time
          description: &gt;-
            Date and time at which the message was  created. &lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to set this field to today's date.
        numberOfTransactions:
          type: string
          pattern: '[0-9]{1,15}$'
          description: &gt;-
            Number of individual transactions contained in the payment info=
rmation group.&lt;br&gt;
            Usage- Caller to set this field to 1 to indicate there's only o=
ne transaction in the payment. For Bulk payment in the future, this field w=
ill need to be set by the caller to the actual number of transactions in th=
e bulk instruction.
        settlementInformation:
          type: object
          required:
            - settlementMethod
          properties:
            settlementMethod:
              type: string
              description: |-
                Method used to settle the (batch of) payment instructions. =
The possible values are:
                - INDA: InstructedAgent. Settlement is done by the agent in=
structed to execute a payment instruction.
                - INGA: InstructingAgent. Settlement is done by the agent i=
nstructing and forwarding the payment to the next party in the payment chai=
n.
                - COVE: CoverMethod. Settlement is done through a cover pay=
ment.
                - CLRG: ClearingSystem. Settlement is done through a paymen=
t clearing system.
              enum:
                - INDA
                - INGA
                - COVE
                - CLRG
            instructingReimbursementAgent:
              type: object
              properties:
                BICFI:
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/BICFI'
            instructedReimbursementAgent:
              type: object
              properties:
                BICFI:
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/BICFI'
        instructingAgent:
          type: object
          properties:
            BICFI:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/BICFI'
        instructedAgent:
          type: object
          properties:
            BICFI:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/BICFI'
        originalGroupInformation:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/OriginalGroupInformationObject'
        transactionInformation:
          type: object
          description: Information concerning the original transactions, to=
 which the return message refers.
          required:
            - returnedInterbankSettlementAmount
            - supplementaryData
          properties:
            returnIdentification:
              type: string
              description: Unique identification, as assigned by an instruc=
ting party for an instructed party, to unambiguously identify the returned =
transaction.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 35
              pattern: ^[0-9a-f]{8}([0-9a-f]{4}){3}[0-9a-f]{12}$
            originalInstructionIdentification:
              type: string
              description: Unique identification, as assigned by the origin=
al instructing party for the original instructed party, to unambiguously id=
entify the original instruction.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 35
            originalEndToEndIdentification:
              type: string
              description: Unique identification, as assigned by the origin=
al initiating party, to unambiguously identify the original transaction.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 35
            originalTransactionIdentification:
              type: string
              description: Unique identification, as assigned by the origin=
al first instructing agent, to unambiguously identify the transaction.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 35
            originalInterbankSettlementAmount:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/CurrencyAndAmount'
            returnedInterbankSettlementAmount:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/CurrencyAndAmount'
            returnedInstructedAmount:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/CurrencyAndAmount'
            interbankSettlementDate:
              type: string
              format : date
              description: Date on which the amount of money ceases to be a=
vailable to the agent that owes it and when the amount of money becomes ava=
ilable to the agent to which it is due.
            chargeBearer:
              type: string
              description: |-
                Specifies which party/parties will bear the charges associa=
ted with the processing of the payment transaction. The possible values are=
:
                - DEBT: BorneByDebtor. All transaction charges are to be bo=
rne by the debtor.
                - CRED: BorneByCreditor. All transaction charges are to be =
borne by the creditor.
                - SHAR: Shared. In a credit transfer context, means that tr=
ansaction charges on the sender side are to be borne by the debtor, transac=
tion charges on the receiver side are to be borne by the creditor. In a dir=
ect debit context, means that transaction charges on the sender side are to=
 be borne by the creditor, transaction charges on the receiver side are to =
be borne by the debtor.
                - SLEV: FollowingServiceLevel. Charges are to be applied fo=
llowing the rules agreed in the service level and/or scheme.
              enum:
                - DEBT
                - CRED
                - SHAR
                - SLEV
            chargesInformation:
              type: array
              description: Provides information on the charges to be paid b=
y the charge bearer(s) related to the processing of the return transaction.
              items:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Charges'

            returnReasonInformation:
              type: array
              description: Provides detailed information on the return reas=
on.
              items:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/PaymentReturnReason'
            settlementPriority:
              type: string
              description: |-
                Indicator of the urgency or order of importance that the in=
structing party would like the instructed party to apply to the processing =
of the settlement instruction.
                Usage: the SettlementPriority is the settlement priority of=
 the return message, and not of the original instruction. The possible valu=
es are:
                - URGT: Urgent. Priority level is urgent (highest priority =
possible).
                - HIGH: High. Priority level is high.
                - NORM: Normal. Priority level is normal.
              enum:
                - URGT
                - HIGH
                - NORM
            originalTransactionReference:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/OriginalTransactionReference'
            supplementaryData:
              type: object
              description: Additional information that cannot be captured i=
n the structured elements and/or any other specific block.
              required:
                - paymentId
              properties:
                paymentId:
                  type: string
                  description: "Payment Identifier, also known as Receipt N=
umber. Caller to generate a 15-character string as per the format"
                  minLength: 1
                  maxLength: 36
                originalPaymentId:
                  type: string
                  description: Payment Identifier, also known as Receipt Nu=
mber, of the original payment.
                  minLength: 1
                  maxLength: 36
                groupCase:
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/caseObject'
                OFICase:
                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/caseObject'
                cancellationReasonCode:
                  type: string
                  description: Cancellation Reason Code for the return, as =
applicable.
                  maxLength: 4
                alternateFundingAccount:
                  type: object
                  description: Provides the details to identify the alterna=
te funding account from where the debit for this payment return should be p=
osted.
                  properties:
                    identification:
                      type: string
                      description: Identification assigned by an institutio=
n.
                      minLength: 1
                      maxLength: 34
                    schemeName:
                      type: string
                      description: Name of the identification scheme, in a =
coded form as published in an external list.
                      minLength: 1
                      maxLength: 4
                    name:
                      type: string
                      description: Name of the account, as assigned by the =
account servicing institution, in agreement with the account owner in order=
 to provide an additional means of identification of the account.
                      minLength: 1
                      maxLength: 70
                originalCreditorAdditionalData:
                  type: object
                  properties:
                    FLAN:
                      type: string
                      description: Full Legal Account Name of the original =
creditor account (i.e. debtor account for this payment return), as assigned=
 by the bank, in order to provide an additional means of identification of =
the account.
                      minLength: 1
                      maxLength: 140
                    birthOrIncorporationDate:
                      type: string
                      format : date
                      description: Date on which the original creditor (i.e=
. debtor for this payment return) is born. If company, it is the date of in=
corporation.
                    birthOrIncorporationPlace:
                      type: string
                      description: Place where the original creditor (i.e. =
debtor for this payment return) was born. If company, it is the place of in=
corporation.
                      minLength: 1
                      maxLength: 35
                    addressLine:
                      type: array
                      description: Address in which the original creditor (=
i.e. debtor for this payment return) resides. In the case of a company, it =
is the address from which the affairs of that company are directed.
                      maxItems: 7
                      items:
                        type: string
                        maxLength: 35
                    ABN:
                      type: string
                      description: Australian Business Number of the origin=
al creditor (i.e. debtor for this payment return).
                      minLength: 1
                      maxLength: 35


    creator:
      type: object
      required:
        - BICFI
      properties:
        BICFI:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/BICFI'
    caseObject:
      type: object
      required:
        - identification
      properties:
        identification:
          type: string
          description: Internal Case management system reference id or OFI =
case reference for an NPP payment return.
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 35
        creator:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/creator'

    OriginalGroupInformationObject:
      type: object
      description: Provides information on the original group, to which the=
 message refers.
      required:
        - originalMessageIdentification
        - originalMessageNameIdentification
      properties:
        originalMessageIdentification:
          type: string
          description: Point to point reference, as assigned by the origina=
l instructing party, to unambiguously identify the original message.
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 35
        originalMessageNameIdentification:
          type: string
          description: Specifies the original message name identifier to wh=
ich the message refers.
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 35
        originalCreationDateTime:
          type: string
          format: date-time
          description: Date and time at which the original message was crea=
ted.

    BICFI:
      type: string
      description: Code allocated to a financial institution by the ISO 936=
2 Registration Authority as described in ISO 9362 "Banking - Banking teleco=
mmunication messages - Business identifier code (BIC)".
      pattern: '[A-Z]{6,6}[A-Z2-9][A-NP-Z0-9]([A-Z0-9]{3,3}){0,1}'

    Charges:
      type: object
      description: Set of elements used to provide information on the charg=
es related to the payment transaction.
      properties:
        agent:
          type: object
          description: Agent that takes the transaction charges or to which=
 the transaction charges are due.
          properties:
            BICFI:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/BICFI'
        amount:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/CurrencyAndAmount'

    CurrencyAndAmount:
      type: object
      description: A number of monetary units specified in an active or a h=
istoric currency where the unit of currency is explicit and compliant with =
ISO 4217.
      required:
        - amount
        - currency
      properties:
        currency:
          type: string
          minLength: 3
          maxLength: 3
          description: Unit of currency compliant with ISO 4217.
        amount:
          type: string
          pattern: '\d{1,13}\.?\d{0,3}$'
          description: Amount of money, as provided in the original transac=
tion, settled between the instructing agent and the instructed agent.

    PaymentReturnReason:
      type: object
      description: Provides further details on the reason of the return of =
the transaction.
      properties:
        reason:
          type: string
          description: Reason for the return, as published in an external r=
eason code list.
          maxLength: 4
        additionalInformation:
          type: array
          description: Further details on the return reason.
          items:
            type: string
            maxItems: 3

    OriginalTransactionReference:
      type: object
      description: Key elements used to refer the original transaction.
      required:
        - debtorAccount
        - creditorAccount
      properties:
        interbankSettlementAmount:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/CurrencyAndAmount'
        interbankSettlementDate:
          type: string
          format : date
          description: Date on which the amount of money ceases to be avail=
able to the agent that owes it and when the amount of money becomes availab=
le to the agent to which it is due.
        paymentTypeInformation:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/PaymentTypeInformation'
        remittanceInformation:
          type: object
          properties:
            unstructured:
              type: array
              maxItems: 2
              description: Information supplied to enable the matching/reco=
nciliation of an entry with the items that the payment is intended to settl=
e, such as commercial invoices in an accounts'' receivable system.
              items:
                type: string
                maxLength: 140
        debtor:
          type: object
          description: Set of elements used to identify a person or an orga=
nisation.
          properties:
            name:
              type: string
              description: Name by which a party is known, and which is usu=
ally used to identify sending party.
              maxLength: 140
            identification:
              type: string
              description: Unique and unambiguous identification of a perso=
n.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 35
            issuer:
              type: string
              description: Entity that assigns the identification.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 35
        debtorAccount:
          type: object
          description: Provides the details to identify an account.
          required:
            - identification
          properties:
            identification:
              type: string
              description: Identification assigned by an institution.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 34
            schemeName:
              type: string
              description: Sets of elements to identify a name of the ident=
ification scheme.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 4
            issuer:
              type: string
              description: Entity that assigns the identification.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 35
            name:
              type: string
              description: Name of the account, as assigned by the account =
servicing institution, in agreement with the account owner in order to prov=
ide an additional means of identification of the account.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 70
        debtorAgent:
          type: object
          description: Set of elements used to uniquely and unambiguously i=
dentify a financial institution or a branch of a financial institution.
          properties:
            BICFI:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/BICFI'
        creditor:
          type: object
          description: Set of elements used to identify a person or an orga=
nisation.
          properties:
            name:
              type: string
              description: Name by which a party is known and which is usua=
lly used to identify that party.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 140
            identification:
              type: string
              description: Identification assigned by an institution.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 35
            issuer:
              type: string
              description: Entity that assigns the identification.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 35
        creditorAccount:
          type: object
          description: Provides the details to identify an account.
          required:
            - identification
          properties:
            identification:
              type: string
              description: Identification assigned by an institution.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 34
            schemeName:
              type: string
              description: Name of the identification scheme, in a coded fo=
rm as published in an external list.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 4
            issuer:
              type: string
              description: Entity that assigns the identification.
              minLength: 1
              maxLength: 35
        creditorAgent:
          type: object
          description: Set of elements used to uniquely and unambiguously i=
dentify a financial institution or a branch of a financial institution.
          properties:
            BICFI:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/BICFI'
        ultimateDebtorName:
          type: string
          description: Name by which a party is known and which is usually =
used to identify that party.
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 140
        ultimateCreditorName:
          type: string
          description: Name by which a party is known and which is usually =
used to identify that party.
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 140

    PaymentTypeInformation:
      type: object
      properties:
        serviceLevel:
          type: string
          description: Specifies a pre-agreed service or level of service b=
etween the parties.
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 35
        localInstrument:
          type: string
          description: Specifies the type of local instrument being request=
ed by the initiating party.
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 35
        categoryPurpose:
          type: string
          description: Specifies the high-level purpose of the instruction =
based on a set of pre-defined categories. This is used by the initiating pa=
rty to provide information concerning the processing of the payment.
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 35
        instructionPriority:
          type: string
          description: |-
            Indicator of the urgency or order of importance that the instru=
cting party would like the instructed party to apply to the processing of t=
he instruction. The possible values are:
            - HIGH: High. Priority level is high.
            - NORM: Normal. Priority level is normal.
          enum:
            - HIGH
            - NORM

    PaymentReturnResponse:
      type: object
      properties:
        data:
          type: object
          properties:
            paymentReturnStatusReport:
              $ref: "#/components/schemas/PaymentReturnStatusObject"

    PaymentReturnStatusObject:
      type: object
      description: Synchronous response to Submit Payment Return Request.
      required:
        - messageIdentification
      properties:
        messageIdentification:
          type: string
          description: |-
            Point to point reference, as assigned by the instructing party,=
 and sent to the next party in the chain to unambiguously identify the mess=
age.
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 35
        creationDateTime:
          type: string
          format : date-time
          description: Date and time at which the message was created.
        groupInformation:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/GroupInformationObject'
        transactionInformation:
          type: object
          description: Provides information on the original transactions to=
 which the status report message refers.
          properties:
            transactionStatus:
              type: string
              description: Specifies the ISO status of the credit transacti=
on within the payment, in case of on-us payments.
                &lt;br&gt;
                Usage-  Possible values-
                ACSC - Accepted Settlement Completed (success)
                RJCT - Rejected (posting rejected)
                ACSP - Accepted Settlement In Process (auto retry in progre=
ss in case of technical failure
            statusReasonInformation:
              type: array
              items:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/statusReasonInformation'
            supplementaryData:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/supplementaryDataResponseObject'

  responses:
    200healthCheckStatusResponse:
      description: healthcheck status
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/healthCheckStatus'
    201PostPaymentIDGenerationResponse:
      description: |
        __Successful Operation__
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: "#/components/schemas/PaymentIDResponse"
    202PostPaymentsResponse:
      description: |
        __Intermediate State__
        Possible Partial Errors:
        &lt;table&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Message&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Description&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;2002&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;The request is placed in a store-and-forward queue fo=
r later processing.&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
        &lt;/table&gt;
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: "#/components/schemas/PaymentInitiationResponse"

    201PostPaymentsResponse:
      description: |
        __Successful Operation__
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: "#/components/schemas/PaymentInitiationResponse"

    400PostPaymentsErrorResponse:
      description: |
        __Bad Request__

        Possible errors:
        &lt;table&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Code&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Message&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Description&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;2000&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Invalid Input Parameter&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;The given {parameterName} has missing/invalid value&l=
t;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;2001&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Downstream Error&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;[{Error message from downstream}]&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
        &lt;/table&gt;
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorResponse'
          example:
            result:
              errors:
                - code: 2001
                  message: Missing request parameter
                  details: At least parameter should be present

    400getPaymentsIdGenerationErrorResponse:
      description: |
        __Bad Request__

        Possible errors:
        &lt;table&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Code&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Message&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Description&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;2000&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Invalid Input Parameter&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;{ Validation error detail }&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
        &lt;/table&gt;
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorResponse'
          example:
            result:
              errors:
                - code: 2000
                  message: Invalid Input Parameter
                  details: The given channelId has missing/invalid value
    500PaymentsIdGenerationErrorResponse:
      description: |
        __Bad Request__

        Possible errors:
        &lt;table&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Code&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Message&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Description&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
         &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;10003&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Unknown/Runtime Exception occurred&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Unknown/Runtime Exception occurred during the API exe=
cution&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
        &lt;/table&gt;
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorResponse'
          example:
            result:
              errors:
                - code: 10003
                  message: Unknown/Runtime Exception occurred
                  details: Unknown/Runtime Exception occurred during the AP=
I execution
    500ErrorResponse:
      description: |
        __Internal Server Error__
        Possible errors:
        &lt;table&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Code&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Message&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Description&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;10001&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Host Unavailable&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;The downstream system failed to accept the request&lt=
;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;10002&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Provider Timeout&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;The downstream system failed to respond within the ex=
pected time periods&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;10003&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Unknown/Runtime Exception occurred&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Unknown/Runtime Exception occurred during the API exe=
cution&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;10004&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Downstream System Error&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;[{Error message from downstream}]&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
        &lt;/table&gt;
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorResponse'
          example:
            result:
              errors:
                - code: 10003
                  message: Unknown/Runtime Exception occurred
                  details: Unknown/Runtime Exception occurred during the AP=
I execution

    201PostPaymentReturnResponse:
      description: |
        __Successful Operation__
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: "#/components/schemas/PaymentReturnResponse"

    400PaymentsReturnErrorResponse:
      description: |
        __Bad Request__

        Possible errors:
        &lt;table&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Code&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Message&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Error Description&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;2000&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Invalid Input Parameter&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;{ Validation error detail }&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
          &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;2001&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;Downstream Validation Error&lt;/td&gt;
            &lt;td&gt;{ Error message from downstream }&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;/tr&gt;
        &lt;/table&gt;
      content:
        application/json:
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/ErrorResponse'
          example:
            result:
              errors:
                - code: 2000
                  message: Invalid Input Parameter
                  details: The given userId has missing/invalid value

  parameters:
    brandSilo:
      name: brandSilo
      in: query
      description: |
        The Brand Silo the caller is operating in. Brand Silo is a concept =
used in Westpac to segregate Customer records based on a combination of the=
 organisation that =E2=80=9Cowns=E2=80=9D the customer relationship and the=
 systems environment in which their identity records are created and mainta=
ined. A Brand Silo is a classification whereas a Brand is a descriptive ent=
ity associated with an Organisation.&lt;br&gt;
        Usage- Caller to set this field to 'WPAC'.
      required: true
      schema:
        type: string
        enum:
          - WPAC
          - SGBBSA
    customerType:
      name: customerType
      in: query
      description: |
        The type of Involved Party.&lt;br&gt;
        Usage- Caller to set the appropriate customer type.
      required: true
      schema:
        type: string
        enum:
          - Individual
          - Organisation
    idempotencyKey:
      in: header
      name: x-idempotency-key
      description:
        In the presence of failures, channel may send a certain request mul=
tiple times to ensure it is accepted. The processing system ensures that pa=
yment initiation is idempotent by relying on this idempotency key. Multiple=
 requests that have the same idempotency key will be considered by the proc=
essing system to be retries and not as different payments. Every request wi=
ll be processed only once per x-idempotency-key.&lt;br&gt;
       =20
        Usage- Caller to generate a unique identifier GUID (Globally unique=
 message identifier) to support idempotency checks.
      required: true
      schema:
        type: string
        pattern: ^[0-9a-f]{8}-([0-9a-f]{4}-){3}[0-9a-f]{12}$
    userId:
      in: header
      name: x-userId
      description:
        The unique identifier for the user invoking the API (eg. Staff sala=
ry number, Customer CIS/GCIS key, Partner CIS/GCIS key or other identifier)=
.&lt;br&gt;
       =20
        Usage- Caller to map the appropriate user id.
      required: true
      schema:
        type: string
        pattern: '^[0-9A-Za-z]{1,100}$'
    userIdScheme:
      in: header
      name: x-userIdScheme
      description:
        The scheme (type) applicable for the user identifier of the consume=
r invoking the API.&lt;br&gt;
       =20
        Usage- Caller to set the appropriate user id scheme.
      required: true
      schema:
        type: string
        enum:
          - StaffSalaryNumber
          - CustomerInternalId
          - CustomerNumber
          - SystemProcess</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
